 :tx/rationale "Create task: FUTURE-2: Learned ACP context precedence — track which context blocks agents USE and auto-promote/demote (SEED.md S7, INV-GUIDANCE-005). BACKGROUND: ACP context blocks have static precedence (System > Methodology > UserRequested > Speculative > Ambient). But some blocks are consistently useful (agents act on boundary coverage info) while others are consistently ignored (agents never read methodology gaps). Significance accumulation (SEED.md S7, AS-007) can be applied to context blocks: track which blocks appear in output → did the agent's next action reference information from that block? Blocks with high correlation to agent behavior get promoted; low-correlation blocks get demoted. This is the RFL feedback loop applied to OUTPUT QUALITY rather than routing. Uses the same action-outcome tracking infrastructure from RFL-1..3. APPROACH: Extend :action/* schema with :action/context-blocks-shown (String, JSON list of block precedences). In the outcome classification (RFL-3), additionally check if the agent's next command references content from specific blocks. Accumulate per-block follow-through rates. Reorder blocks by learned precedence. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-005, SEED.md S7."
